    "def calculate_letter_proba(letter: str, data: list = words_list, n_letters: int = 5) -> list:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculates the probability of a given letter occurring at a given position in a list of words.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        letter (str): The letter for which the probability is calculated.\n",
    "        data (list): The list of words to analyze (default: words_list).\n",
    "        n_letters (int): The number of letters in each word to consider (default: 5).\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        A list of probabilities, where the i-th element is the probability of the given letter occurring in the i-th position.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    letter = letter.lower()\n",
    "    proba_list = []\n",
    "    for i in range(n_letters):\n",
    "        found = 0\n",
    "        count = 0\n",
    "        for word in data:\n",
    "            if letter == word[i]:\n",
    "                found +=1\n",
    "            count += 1\n",
    "        proba_list.append(found / count)\n",
    "    return proba_list"
   ]
  },

    "def calculate_sum_prob(word: str, df: pd.DataFrame) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculates the sum of probabilities of each unique letter in a given word occurring in a Pandas DataFrame.\n",
    "    When a letter repeats in a word, the function sums only its single highest value.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        word (str): The word for which the probability is calculated.\n",
    "        df (pd.DataFrame): The DataFrame containing probabilities for each letter in each position.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Sum of probabilities of each unique letter in the given word (float).\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    word = word.lower()\n",
    "    # Penalizing the results for the letters \"ę\", \"ą\", \"y\", \"i\" if they are at the end of a word,\n",
    "    # because they indicate a variant or plural that rarely appear in the game.\n",
    "    punish_endings = [\"ę\",\"ą\",\"y\",\"i\"]\n",
    "    prob_dict = []\n",
    "    used_letters = set()\n",
    "    sword = [*word]\n",
    "    for index, letter in enumerate(sword):\n",
    "        if letter in punish_endings and index == 4:\n",
    "            prob_dict.append({letter : df.loc[letter, index] / 2 })\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            prob_dict.append({letter : df.loc[letter, index]})\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # Penalizing repeated letters   \n",
    "    unique_letters = {}\n",
    "    for i in prob_dict:\n",
    "        for key, value in i.items():\n",
    "            if key not in unique_letters:\n",
    "                unique_letters[key] = value\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                if value > unique_letters[key]:\n",
    "                    x = unique_letters[key]\n",
    "                    unique_letters[key] = value + x / 2\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    unique_letters[key] += value / 2\n",
    "    return (sum(unique_letters.values()))"
   ]
  },

    "def calculate_proba(data: list) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Creates a DataFrame of probabilities of each word in given set of data.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        data (list): The list of words for which the probability is calculated.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        A sorted list of tuples, each containing a word from the data set and its total probability in the data set.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    unique_letters = sorted(list(set(\"\".join(data))))\n",
    "    letter_prob = [calculate_letter_proba(letter, data) for letter in unique_letters]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    df = pd.DataFrame(data = letter_prob, columns = [num for num in range(5)])\n",
    "    df[\"letter\"] = unique_letters\n",
    "    df.set_index(\"letter\", inplace=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    word_prob_list = [(i, calculate_sum_prob(i, df)) for i in data]\n",
    "    return sorted(word_prob_list, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)"
   ]
  },

    "def draw_heatmap(data: list) -> None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Draws a heatmap based on the given data.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        data (list): A list of words.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        None.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    unique_letters = sorted(list(set(\"\".join(data))))\n",
    "    letter_prob = [calculate_letter_proba(letter, data) for letter in unique_letters]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    df = pd.DataFrame(data = letter_prob, columns = [num for num in range(5)])\n",
    "    df[\"letter\"] = unique_letters\n",
    "    df.set_index(\"letter\", inplace=True)\n",
    "    df.sort_values(4,ascending = False).head(10)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 16), dpi=200)\n",
    "    g = sns.heatmap(df, annot=True, linewidth=.5, cmap=sns.cubehelix_palette(as_cmap=True))\n",
    "    g.set_xticklabels(['Position 1','Position 2','Position 3','Position 4','Position 5'])\n",
    "    g.xaxis.tick_top()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]

    "def green_letters(user_input: str, data: list) -> list:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Return a list of words from data that match the letters indicated in user_input.\n",
    "    If the user after typing the word received a green letter E on the second position \n",
    "    input  would look like this: \"-E---\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    user_input (str): A string containing letters that the user has inputted.\n",
    "    data (list): A list of words to filter by.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    list: A list of words from the input list that match the user's revealed letters.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    user_input = user_input.lower()\n",
    "    for index, letter in enumerate(user_input):\n",
    "        if letter != \"-\":\n",
    "            data = [i for i in data if i[index] == letter]\n",
    "    return  data"
   ]
  },

    "def yellow_letters(user_input: str, data: list = words_list) -> list:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Return a list of words from data that match the letters indicated in user_input.\n",
    "    If the user after typing the word received a yellow letter B on the first position \n",
    "    input  would look like this: \"B----\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    user_input (str): A string containing letters that the user has inputted.\n",
    "    data (list): A list of words to filter by.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    list: A list of words from the input list that match the user's revealed letters.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    user_input = user_input.lower()\n",
    "    for index, letter in enumerate(user_input):\n",
    "        if letter != \"-\":\n",
    "            data = [i for i in data if letter in i if i[index] != letter]\n",
    "    return data"
   ]

    "def grey_letters(user_input: str, data: list) -> list:\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    The function takes a list of words and returns a list of words that do not contain the letters indicated in user_input.\n",
    "    If the user after typing the word received a grey letters A, B and C on the any position\n",
    "    input  would look like this: \"ABC\" (the order doesn't matter)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        user_input (str): A string containing the grey letters.\n",
    "        data (list): A list of words to filter by.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        A list of words that don't contain any of the grey letters.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    user_input = user_input.lower()\n",
    "    g_letters = [*user_input]\n",
    "    new_data = []\n",
    "    if user_input:\n",
    "        for word in data:\n",
    "            if all(letter not in word for letter in g_letters):\n",
    "                new_data.append(word)\n",
    "    return new_data"
   ]
  },

    "def literalnie_solver(data, green: str = \"-----\", yellow: str = \"-----\", grey: str = \"\") -> list:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Function solves a literal puzzle based on given green, yellow, and grey letters.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "    - data: a list of words to be filtered\n",
    "    - green: a string representing green letters in the puzzle\n",
    "    - yellow: a string representing yellow letters in the puzzle\n",
    "    - grey: a string representing grey letters in the puzzle\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    - A list of words\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    data = green_letters(green, data)\n",
    "    data = yellow_letters(yellow, data)\n",
    "    data = grey_letters(grey, data)\n",
    "    return data"
   ]
  },
